  "posts": [
    {
      "id": "note-agentic-garden",
      "kind": "note",
      "slug": "agentic-garden",
      "date": "2026-03-26",
      "title": {
        "zh-CN": "把个人站重构成内容操作系统",
        "en": "Turning a portfolio into a content operating system"
      },
      "summary": {
        "zh-CN": "页面应该只负责显示，内容与工作流应该在本地工具链中可维护、可重建、可发布。",
        "en": "The page should only render; the content and workflow should remain maintainable, rebuildable, and releasable in local tooling."
      },
      "tags": [
        "portfolio",
        "workflow",
        "agents"
      ],
      "body": {
        "zh-CN": "把作品集当成一个静态页面很容易，但那通常意味着内容会慢慢再次被写死回代码里。\n\n我更想把它做成一个本地优先的内容操作系统：\n\n- 页面只负责渲染已经整理好的 bundle。\n- 简历、短文、长文都来自统一的 YAML 与 Markdown。\n- CLI、Skill、Studio GUI 复用同一套 schema 与服务层。\n- 发布之前必须通过校验、类型检查和页面回归。\n\n这样每一次内容更新都不是“改页面”，而是“运行一次可靠的内容工作流”。",
        "en": "It is easy to treat a portfolio as a static page, but that usually means the content slowly leaks back into hardcoded UI strings.\n\nI want this project to act more like a local-first content operating system:\n\n- The page should only render a generated bundle.\n- Resumes, notes, and articles should come from shared YAML and Markdown sources.\n- The CLI, Skill, and Studio GUI should reuse the same schema and services.\n- Every release should pass validation, type checks, and browser regression coverage.\n\nThat turns each update from “editing the page” into “running a reliable content workflow”."
      },
      "sourcePath": "content/posts/garden/agentic-garden"
    },
    {
      "id": "article-terminal-ide-portfolio",
      "kind": "article",
      "slug": "terminal-ide-portfolio",
      "date": "2026-03-26",
      "title": {
        "zh-CN": "为什么我的作品集要长得像一台 IDE",
        "en": "Why my portfolio wants to feel like an IDE"
      },
      "summary": {
        "zh-CN": "IDE 风格不是噱头，它天然适合展示工程上下文、内容版本和创作流程。",
        "en": "The IDE aesthetic is not just a gimmick. It is a useful way to expose engineering context, versioned content, and creator workflows."
      },
      "tags": [
        "design",
        "tui",
        "portfolio"
      ],
      "body": {
        "zh-CN": "# 为什么我的作品集要长得像一台 IDE\n\n很多作品集首页都在做同一件事：把信息铺平、把经历压缩、把表达变成几个通用卡片。\n\n我更喜欢把个人站做成一台可以被阅读的“工作环境”。\n\n## IDE 风格适合展示什么\n\n- 它天然支持“文件与模块”的心智模型。\n- 它允许内容带着上下文一起出现，而不是孤立地摆在页面上。\n- 它能把经历、项目、短文、长文和本地创作工具放到同一个叙事空间里。\n\n## 为什么这次要做配置驱动\n\n过去很多个人站会把个人信息直接写在前端组件里。短期很快，长期会让内容更新越来越难。\n\n这次重构的目标是：\n\n1. 所有可维护内容都进入 YAML / Markdown。\n2. 页面只渲染 bundle，不直接持有个人信息。\n3. 本地 CLI 与 Studio GUI 负责导入、整理、预览与发布。\n4. 发布前自动跑校验、类型检查和浏览器回归。\n\n## 结果会是什么\n\n作品集不再只是一个“展示结果”的页面，而是一个“生成结果”的系统。",
        "en": "# Why my portfolio wants to feel like an IDE\n\nMany portfolio homepages do the same thing: flatten information, compress experience, and turn expression into a few familiar cards.\n\nI prefer treating a personal site like a readable working environment.\n\n## What the IDE aesthetic gives me\n\n- A natural mental model for files, modules, and context.\n- A place where experience, projects, notes, and articles can live together.\n- A visual language that feels closer to how I actually work.\n\n## Why this rebuild is config-first\n\nHardcoding personal information into UI components is fast in the short term, but expensive to maintain over time.\n\nThis refactor aims to:\n\n1. Move every maintainable content fragment into YAML and Markdown.\n2. Make the page render a generated bundle instead of owning raw personal data.\n3. Let the local CLI and Studio GUI handle import, normalization, preview, and release.\n4. Run validation, type checking, and browser regression before publishing.\n\n## The outcome\n\nThe portfolio stops being a page that merely shows results and becomes a system that produces them."
      },
      "sourcePath": "content/posts/articles/terminal-ide-portfolio"
    }
